sysbench
========

A system benchmark tool written in Rust. Measures CPU, network, and storage.


BENCHMARKS
----------

  CPU      - Hex digits of pi via Bailey-Borwein-Plouffe formula.
             Runs single-threaded and multi-threaded, averages 3 runs each.

  Network  - Download (100 MB) and upload (50 MB) via Cloudflare speed test.

  Storage  - Sequential write + read of a 1 GB file in $TMPDIR.


INSTALL
-------

  bash install.sh

  The script will:
    - Offer to install Rust via rustup if not already present
    - Build with native CPU optimisations (LTO, single codegen unit)
    - Install the binary to ~/.local/bin (non-root) or /usr/local/bin (root)


USAGE
-----

  sysbench

  No arguments. Runs all three suites and prints results to stdout.


BUILD MANUALLY
--------------

  cd tester
  RUSTFLAGS="-C target-cpu=native" cargo build --release
  ./target/release/sysbench


